p: The data were analyzed by a one-way analysis of variance (ANOVA) using the SPSS program (IBM SPSS Statistics 22.0). The measurement of the difference was determined using Scheffe’s multiple range test. Values of P < 0.05 were considered statistically significant. Assays were performed in triplicate, and the results were expressed as the mean (±SE). The EC 50 values were calculated using probit analysis.
